sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM terrorist_attacks
WHERE attack_type = 'Shooting';

SELECT school_id, COUNT(attack_id) AS attack_count
FROM terrorist_attacks
GROUP BY school_id;

external_knowledge:
- A province can have multiple cities;
- Each city can have multiple schools;
- The total number of schools is derived by summing up the school counts from all cities.

- 'Blossoming with fewer students' refers to schools with a population below the average population of all schools;
- 'The average bloom' represents the average population of all schools;
- 'Location within the provinces' refers to the province names where these schools are situated.

- "silent witnesses to the storm of terrorism" refers to cities where schools have experienced terrorist attacks;
- "echoes of violence" refers to the incidents of attacks, including the types and dates of attacks, as well as the number of injuries and fatalities;
- "essential facilities" include drinking water, toilets, electricity, internet, libraries, playgrounds, sports facilities, and medical facilities;
- "educational performance" includes the average percentage of boys and girls enrolled, the average dropout rate, and the average graduation rate.

- "Vital ingredients of learning" include drinking water, toilet, electricity, internet, library, playground, sports facilities, and medical facility;
- "Pouring more per student" refers to the budget allocation per student being higher than the average across all schools;
- "Foundational amenities" are the facilities provided by the school, each with a predefined budget value.

- "Average impact of terrorist attacks on schools" refers to the average number of people affected by terrorist attacks in each school;
- "Average graduation rates" refers to the average percentage of students who graduate from each school;
- "Percentage of schools equipped with drinking water facilities" refers to the proportion of schools in each city that have access to clean drinking water.

- "All facilities fully equipped" means that the school has drinking water, toilets, electricity, internet, a library, a playground, sports facilities, and a medical facility;
- "Unmarred by recent acts of violence" means that the last recorded terrorist attack at the school occurred before January 1, 2015;
- "Beacon of educational excellence" refers to the school with the highest number of enrolled students.

- "Population exceeding 300,000" refers to cities with a large number of inhabitants;
- "Dropout rate above the stormy threshold of 10%" implies a significant number of students leaving school before completion;
- "Touched by the shadow of more than one terrorist attack" means the school has experienced more than one terrorist incident.
